name: Spinach Quiche with Cottage Cheese
author: bettina
summary: I don't normally like cooked spinach but I fell in love with this at first bite.  Sooo good!
ingredients: 1 (10 ounce) package frozen chopped spinach, thawed
1 bunch green onions, finely chopped (white parts only)
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Lightly grease a 9 inch pie or quiche pan
Place spinach in a small saucepan
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until soft
Stir in green onions, eggs, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese
Bake uncovered in preheated oven for 45 minutes
Remove from oven and sprinkle with crushed croutons
Return to oven and bake for an additional 15 minutes, until eggs are set
